user_query:
Before I kick off the long training described in input/training_plan.json, run a one‑minute pre‑flight hardware health gate on my Mac using a terminal health checker that reports CPU, RAM, disk, temperature, and an overall status in JSON. Do the following:

1) Take exactly three snapshots spaced ~20 seconds apart using the tool's JSON output. Each snapshot must include: status (ok|warn|critical), cpu_pct, ram_pct, disk_pct, and an ISO8601 timestamp.
2) At the end of the minute, capture the top 5 processes by CPU and the top 5 by RAM.
3) Make a deterministic gate decision: proceed if all three snapshots are ok; wait if any snapshot is warn and none are critical; abort if any snapshot is critical.
4) Write two files:
   - output/preflight_summary.json with this structure:
     {
       "job_name": string,
       "sampled_snapshots": [
         {"status": "ok|warn|critical", "cpu_pct": number, "ram_pct": number, "disk_pct": number, "timestamp": string},
         { ... },
         { ... }
       ],
       "thresholds": {
         "cpu": {"warn": 70, "crit": 90},
         "ram": {"warn": 75, "crit": 90},
         "disk": {"warn": 80, "crit": 90},
         "temp": {"warn": 80, "crit": 95}
       },
       "aggregate_overall": "ok|warn|critical" (the worst of the three snapshot statuses),
       "gate_decision": "proceed|wait|abort",
       "processes": {
         "top_cpu": [ {"pid": string, "cpu": string, "mem": string, "name": string}, ... (5 items) ],
         "top_ram": [ {"pid": string, "mem": string, "cpu": string, "name": string}, ... (5 items) ]
       }
     }
     Ensure the three timestamps are strictly increasing.
   - output/preflight_report.md: a readable report that includes the job name, the gate decision, and a roll‑up of the three snapshots. Use these exact section headings in this order: "Overview", "Snapshots", "Top CPU processes", "Top RAM processes", "Commands Run", and "Recommendations". Under the two Top sections, list at least 5 bullet items each. In "Commands Run", list each shell command you executed to gather data.

Use only relative paths, read the plan from input/, and write only under output/.
